16:45.238 --> 16:47.472
(HOWLING)

16:50.677 --> 16:53.578
(HOWLING)

17:03.890 --> 17:07.458
(HOWLING)

17:07.694 --> 17:10.194
(ALL HOWLING)

17:19.372 --> 17:21.239
(LAUGHING)

17:21.408 --> 17:23.741
Well, all right.
That's great.

17:23.743 --> 17:25.410
You kids want some candy?

17:26.980 --> 17:28.813
Don't know.

17:28.915 --> 17:30.148
Depends, I guess.

17:30.150 --> 17:31.949
MANSON: Depends on what?

17:31.951 --> 17:34.819
Chunky chocolate, taffy bits,
marshmallows?

17:34.821 --> 17:37.555
You... You don't know
if you like that stuff?

17:37.557 --> 17:40.024
-I know I do.
-Course you do.

17:40.026 --> 17:42.193
'Cause you never
got enough.

17:42.195 --> 17:44.796
Mommy and Daddy used it
like a weapon.

17:44.798 --> 17:47.899
Took it away
when you were bad.

17:48.768 --> 17:50.401
(CHUCKLES)

17:51.171 --> 17:53.638
But we're all
good children here.

17:53.640 --> 17:56.040
We get all the candy
we want.

18:00.847 --> 18:04.148
I want some now.
What... What about you?

18:04.451 --> 18:06.451
Yeah, we want some, too.

18:07.987 --> 18:09.487
Good.

18:09.689 --> 18:11.155
Moving on.

18:12.992 --> 18:14.025
Hey.

18:14.027 --> 18:15.927
ROY: She'll be right there.

18:15.929 --> 18:18.963
Thought you said you couldn't
put any weight on that knee.

18:18.965 --> 18:20.364
I can't.

18:20.500 --> 18:22.834
I'll take a little
head, though.

18:23.837 --> 18:26.471
Or maybe a lot. (CHUCKLES)

18:31.878 --> 18:33.678
I know Charlie,
so I know how Charlie goes.

18:33.680 --> 18:36.047
He goes through Roy,
remember?

18:36.216 --> 18:39.117
Go have some candy.
Please.

18:44.624 --> 18:48.059
All right, look, not only
was I here once
already today, Sam,

18:48.061 --> 18:49.193
I don't know where you get off
summoning me

18:49.195 --> 18:50.761
-like somebody's housemaid.
-You're Gladner.

18:50.763 --> 18:51.762
-You're pushing it.
-I'm the killer.

18:51.764 --> 18:54.065
I come up on you
when your back is turned,

18:54.067 --> 18:55.066
and I... Whap, whap!

18:55.068 --> 18:56.801
Both the first and the second
neck wound were fatal.

18:56.803 --> 18:59.036
So after those, he probably
went to his knees
at some point.

18:59.038 --> 19:02.006
-Oh. Okay.
-Took the next five there.

19:02.008 --> 19:04.709
One, two, three, four, five.
And then he's down.

19:04.711 --> 19:07.745
And for the last two,
he was flat on the ground.

19:07.747 --> 19:10.548
-(CHUCKLES)
-Oh, it's funny to you, too?

19:10.550 --> 19:13.117
Watching a man
lose his mind?

19:13.720 --> 19:15.153
Time of death?

19:15.155 --> 19:16.087
Last night.

19:16.089 --> 19:16.888
Mr. Gladner had been dead

19:16.890 --> 19:18.890
about eight, 10 hours
before he was found.

19:18.892 --> 19:21.092
That's eight to 10 hours
before Vickery was seen

19:21.094 --> 19:22.827
-running out of there.
-And he came back.

19:22.829 --> 19:24.629
High as a kite,
dumb as a carp.

19:24.631 --> 19:26.430
Ah, but the downward angles
of the wound

19:26.432 --> 19:28.065
show that the killer
was taller than Gladner.

19:28.067 --> 19:30.134
Vickery is not.
The killer's also a righty.

19:30.136 --> 19:31.669
I've been to
Vickery's apartment,

19:31.671 --> 19:32.603
I saw his crappy guitar.

19:32.605 --> 19:35.206
Pick guard and the bass
"E" string on the wrong side.

19:35.208 --> 19:36.507
He's a lefty.
He is not the guy.

19:36.509 --> 19:38.409
Okay, stop, stop, stop.
When you want to talk

19:38.411 --> 19:40.344
about this like cops
and not these

19:40.346 --> 19:42.580
amateur theatricals,
you let me know.

19:42.582 --> 19:44.749
And you touch me again,
I'm going to pour you out

19:44.751 --> 19:46.117
like a drink.

19:51.057 --> 19:54.959
So, you and Cut
not partners anymore, huh?

19:55.662 --> 19:57.295
Good catch.

20:01.834 --> 20:03.968
(LAUGHTER)

20:55.521 --> 20:58.823
MANSON: Thought maybe
you got lost.

21:01.361 --> 21:05.129
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)
This pad is crazy.

21:05.565 --> 21:08.232
-It yours?
-Nah.

21:08.234 --> 21:10.935
Older lady I met in Frisco.

21:13.106 --> 21:15.640
Devil worship's her trip
at the moment.

21:15.642 --> 21:16.340
(CHUCKLES)

21:16.342 --> 21:18.009
She gave me a standing invite
to this place.

21:18.011 --> 21:21.612
And so when
we came down south,
we just parked the bus here

21:21.614 --> 21:26.350
and joined the preachers,
and the socialites,

21:26.452 --> 21:28.486
and the blood-drinkers.

21:29.122 --> 21:30.855
I saw it, man.

21:30.857 --> 21:33.924
Saw a guy chug some blood.

21:35.028 --> 21:37.161
House is full of people
just like that.

21:37.163 --> 21:41.766
Come here to do what they
don't want to be seen doing.

21:42.902 --> 21:45.469
That the kind of gig
you're into?

21:46.472 --> 21:47.138
I don't know.

21:47.140 --> 21:51.409
This place is full
of a lot of fear and shame.

21:51.411 --> 21:53.344
I don't want that.

21:53.913 --> 21:54.979
I want to stay
feeling good,

21:54.981 --> 22:00.451
and I don't think
good feelings
stick around here.

22:02.121 --> 22:04.255
But I guess we'll see, huh?

22:11.464 --> 22:12.930
Why, hello.

22:17.603 --> 22:18.569
Oh.

22:18.571 --> 22:21.272
Don't you both look good
and worn out.

22:21.274 --> 22:24.408
(CHUCKLES)
How'd she do?

22:26.179 --> 22:29.046
She could learn a thing
or two from Sadie, for sure.

22:31.417 --> 22:33.417
But she'll get there.

22:37.623 --> 22:39.123
Vickery's
a known associate.

22:39.125 --> 22:41.926
His alibi for established
time of death is

22:41.928 --> 22:44.028
he was home alone.
Wow.

22:44.030 --> 22:46.063
He's got a previous
knife assault on his jacket.

22:46.065 --> 22:48.065
He's got a face I want to hit
with a phone book.

22:48.067 --> 22:50.935
And you're making this
about some pissant
rear door key

22:50.937 --> 22:52.670
-and a guitar string, what?
-You arrest Vickery,

22:52.672 --> 22:54.805
you'll just end up
voiding it later.

22:54.807 --> 22:55.673
-It's not him.
-Says you.

22:55.675 --> 22:58.542
Then the real guy's lawyer
will use that voided arrest

22:58.544 --> 23:00.111
-to get the case thrown out.
-Well, if that happens,

23:00.113 --> 23:02.046
you get to say,
"I told you so."
Oh, you'll hate that.

23:02.048 --> 23:04.682
Or you can delegate me to
go find the real guy for you

23:04.684 --> 23:06.150
and then you can take
the credit.

23:06.152 --> 23:08.018
You'll hate that.

23:08.521 --> 23:10.020
Fine. Take a day.

23:10.022 --> 23:11.789
No, take two.

23:11.958 --> 23:13.557
You used to be
more fun, too.

23:13.559 --> 23:16.694
Yeah, a lot of things
used to be more fun.

23:29.709 --> 23:32.276
How'd you know to tell him
about that house?

23:32.745 --> 23:33.778
I didn't.

23:33.780 --> 23:35.346
It just sounds like
a million other places

23:35.348 --> 23:37.648
they've been to
and forgotten.

23:38.885 --> 23:41.318
-Was it real?
-It was.

23:41.320 --> 23:44.255
I went there with my mother,
years ago.

23:44.257 --> 23:46.891
She had a thing for the guy
who owned it.

23:46.893 --> 23:50.461
One night, she called him over
and over, and no answer, so...

23:50.463 --> 23:53.697
She woke me up
and we drove all the way
out there in the dark.

23:53.699 --> 23:54.965
And what happened?

23:54.967 --> 23:57.067
He told her
she should go home.

23:57.069 --> 24:00.938
And what about the, uh...
(HOWLS)

24:03.075 --> 24:05.309
I don't know where
that came from.

24:10.883 --> 24:12.516
I chose.

24:12.919 --> 24:13.684
Charmain...

24:13.686 --> 24:16.153
I'm serious about
being a cop.

24:17.256 --> 24:18.923
About being a great cop.

24:19.325 --> 24:21.425
As serious as you are.

24:22.228 --> 24:23.761
Okay?

24:26.232 --> 24:28.466
-Okay.
-(ENGINE STARTS)

24:28.835 --> 24:31.135
Sam?

24:31.938 --> 24:33.671
(GROANS)

24:33.673 --> 24:35.673
So, I didn't know

24:35.675 --> 24:39.009
if I should read it
or burn it.

24:41.113 --> 24:43.047
Anyway...

24:43.783 --> 24:45.683
I didn't open it.

24:45.685 --> 24:46.817
You're gonna do
what you're gonna do,

24:46.819 --> 24:49.553
but he is not going
back to that place.

24:50.323 --> 24:51.188
Ever.

24:51.190 --> 24:52.723
That, we agree on.

24:52.859 --> 24:54.592
He's going to prison

24:54.694 --> 24:56.360
because of you.

25:11.744 --> 25:13.110
(DOOR OPENING)

25:14.547 --> 25:15.980
All right, look.

25:15.982 --> 25:17.147
I talked to my guy
at Pendleton

25:17.149 --> 25:19.183
who said MPs
don't bother looking nowadays.

25:19.185 --> 25:23.621
There's a couple of
phone calls, goes to file.

25:23.890 --> 25:25.189
Thanks.

25:32.431 --> 25:36.500
<i> # The echo</i>
<i> of a piper's song</i>

25:37.036 --> 25:42.973
<i> # The shadow of a smile</i>

25:43.409 --> 25:47.745
<i> # The shadow</i>
<i> of your smile</i>

25:48.281 --> 25:53.284
<i> # When you are gone</i>

25:53.286 --> 25:57.588
BOTH:
<i> # Will color all my dreams</i>

25:58.457 --> 26:03.794
<i> # And light the dawn #</i>

26:05.765 --> 26:07.831
My mom loved
that song.

26:07.967 --> 26:10.034
Maybe even more
than the movie.

26:10.036 --> 26:11.802
Well, that's what
Charlie was singing,

26:11.804 --> 26:13.871
and he was playing
the guitar.

26:13.873 --> 26:15.806
And when he was done,
he looked at me and said

26:15.808 --> 26:20.277
if I really wanted to,
I could just pick it up
and play it.

26:20.713 --> 26:22.980
Even if I didn't know how.

26:23.649 --> 26:26.116
After my mom died,
I tried everything.

26:26.118 --> 26:29.720
I went to church,
to Evergreen Baptist.

26:29.722 --> 26:33.390
I danced with my top off
in a witches' Sabbath show,

26:33.392 --> 26:35.492
and I was so alone.

26:35.494 --> 26:38.662
But that night,
I left with Charlie.

26:38.664 --> 26:42.866
And he introduced me
to Katie.

26:43.736 --> 26:46.337
And everything was perfect...

26:47.406 --> 26:49.173
Until we met you.

26:52.311 --> 26:53.744
(CHUCKLES)

26:58.918 --> 27:00.584
You're just...

27:00.586 --> 27:01.685
(SIGHS)

27:01.687 --> 27:03.354
So...

27:03.356 --> 27:04.655
Real.

27:05.224 --> 27:08.258
All my friends talk about
back home

27:08.260 --> 27:10.728
is things.

27:12.798 --> 27:13.964
Things they want,

27:13.966 --> 27:17.334
things they have,
things that other people have.

27:18.604 --> 27:19.803
Sometimes

27:19.805 --> 27:22.973
I felt like if I didn't
get away from their voices,

27:22.975 --> 27:26.010
I was actually gonna die.

27:26.646 --> 27:28.479
(MANSON PLAYING GUITAR)

27:32.885 --> 27:34.752
Let's go make ourselves
a demo.

27:35.187 --> 27:36.720
What? Really?

27:36.722 --> 27:38.922
Today we get to start
putting it out there

27:38.924 --> 27:41.025
-all over the world.
-(CHUCKLES)

27:41.027 --> 27:44.395
Oh, my... Charlie!
Where did you find the money?

27:44.397 --> 27:47.531
The money found me.
(STRUMS GUITAR)

27:47.533 --> 27:49.600
(BOTH SQUEALING)

27:50.803 --> 27:52.603
SAM: <i> So what about Manson?</i>

27:52.605 --> 27:55.039
He's in this rundown shack
on Topanga.

27:55.041 --> 27:57.207
Drug den, way station
type of place.

27:57.209 --> 28:00.210
-Mmm-hmm.
-And Emma's there.

28:00.646 --> 28:02.246
-You saw her?
-I did.

28:02.248 --> 28:05.149
If it's the girl
from those photos.

28:05.151 --> 28:08.485
On Gladner, there's a suspect.
It's your boy, Vickery.

28:08.487 --> 28:09.553
-Vic?
-Yeah.

28:09.555 --> 28:10.854
Just being held, not arrested.

28:10.856 --> 28:11.689
Cut thinks he's the guy,

28:11.691 --> 28:13.624
but he's giving me
a grace period.

28:13.626 --> 28:16.326
-Well, is he?
-May not end up mattering,

28:16.328 --> 28:17.895
but no.

28:32.378 --> 28:34.445
You seen this girl?

28:36.182 --> 28:38.849
Anybody seen this girl?

28:40.653 --> 28:42.186
Anybody?

28:45.591 --> 28:48.058
Have you seen her?
This girl?

28:49.895 --> 28:52.062
(POP MUSIC PLAYING ON STEREO)

29:05.044 --> 29:07.144
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

29:10.349 --> 29:12.216
Hey.

29:13.419 --> 29:15.519
Hey.

29:17.356 --> 29:19.389
You seen this girl?

29:20.860 --> 29:23.827
-Lots of girls here.
-That a no?

29:23.829 --> 29:25.295
I don't know what it is.

29:25.297 --> 29:26.864
Better look again.

29:29.702 --> 29:30.634
(CHUCKLES)

29:30.636 --> 29:32.636
If you think
she could have been here,

29:32.638 --> 29:35.139
odds are she probably
was here.

29:35.775 --> 29:37.775
And I might have seen her.

29:37.777 --> 29:39.743
But she's not here now.

29:40.446 --> 29:41.612
Okay.

29:41.614 --> 29:43.280
Yeah, sorry, Officer.

29:43.282 --> 29:45.449
Wish I could've been
more help.

29:45.451 --> 29:49.052
Oh, you seem like
a very helpful guy.

30:05.237 --> 30:07.171
How old are you?

30:07.173 --> 30:09.406
I'll be 16 in December.

30:09.842 --> 30:11.542
Does anyone know
where you are?

30:11.544 --> 30:12.376
(CHUCKLES)

30:12.378 --> 30:17.481
Yeah, um,
this is a letter from my mom.

30:17.483 --> 30:20.184
She says it's okay
for me to be here.

30:20.186 --> 30:21.985
She knows.

30:26.425 --> 30:27.925
(CHUCKLES)

30:33.165 --> 30:34.264
Emma's not here.
She was here...

30:34.266 --> 30:36.500
I have to go.
We have to go.

30:43.008 --> 30:45.442
(HORN HONKING)

30:50.983 --> 30:52.416
(LAUGHS)

30:52.418 --> 30:53.884
Come on.

30:56.522 --> 30:58.722
This is such
a beautiful day.

30:58.724 --> 31:00.557
RUE: Yeah.

31:01.627 --> 31:03.527
This is Charlie.

31:06.298 --> 31:08.432
Rue Fisher.
I'm the engineer.

31:08.434 --> 31:10.534
You come to make some music
with us, Rue?

31:11.437 --> 31:12.302
You're gonna make it, man.

31:12.304 --> 31:14.504
I'm just gonna lay it down
for you.

31:14.506 --> 31:15.138
(CHUCKLES)

31:15.140 --> 31:19.109
But, uh, you really sure this
is where you want to record?

31:19.111 --> 31:22.579
Yeah.
Yeah, you know why?

31:23.015 --> 31:25.482
Because this is where
it is, man.

31:25.484 --> 31:26.116
(LAUGHS)

31:26.118 --> 31:29.086
It's just, we're gonna pick up
a lot of ambient sound.

31:29.088 --> 31:31.889
You mean, we're gonna
pick up everything around us?

31:31.891 --> 31:34.992
Well, hey, man,
that's exactly how we like it.

31:34.994 --> 31:37.828
-(LAUGHS)
-It's just not the
best for, uh...

31:37.830 --> 31:38.829
Rue, man.

31:38.831 --> 31:40.831
Rue-fus, Rue-the-day...

31:42.201 --> 31:44.935
We are ready
when you are, man.

31:45.204 --> 31:46.637
(STRUMS GUITAR)

31:47.840 --> 31:49.973
It was just
bad timing. I...
I'll be there next time,

31:49.975 --> 31:53.443
-or I'll have
someone there...
-Who were all those people?

31:53.445 --> 31:54.344
That house...

31:54.346 --> 31:57.080
Are there places like that
everywhere?

31:57.149 --> 31:58.982
Now, yeah.

31:59.151 --> 31:59.983
(SIGHS)

31:59.985 --> 32:02.019
What is happening?

32:03.389 --> 32:07.024
You know, I couldn't stop
thinking about
her somewhere

32:07.159 --> 32:11.895
lost, being hurt,
crying for me.

32:12.097 --> 32:13.997
I thought all we had to do
was find her,

32:13.999 --> 32:17.834
and now...
I don't know anything.

32:23.442 --> 32:25.108
What?

32:25.277 --> 32:27.311
What is it?

32:28.147 --> 32:30.147
My son is missing.

32:33.185 --> 32:34.785
Oh, Sam.

32:36.388 --> 32:39.456
You know, it... It doesn't
necessarily mean anything.

32:39.458 --> 32:42.960
Our neighbors,
the Rensselaers, their son
was reported dead,

32:42.962 --> 32:45.595
and then two months later,
Ann got a letter from him.

32:45.597 --> 32:49.266
He'd been in the hospital,
but no one had bothered

32:49.268 --> 32:50.934
to tell him it was...

32:50.936 --> 32:54.771
Oh, God, this story is not
helping at all, is it?

32:54.773 --> 32:56.807
No. Thanks.

33:38.650 --> 33:42.252
<i> # You must live</i>
<i> to find love</i>

33:42.821 --> 33:46.823
<i> # And you will try</i>
<i> many times</i>

33:49.194 --> 33:52.295
<i> # But your heart</i>
<i> is still young</i>

33:52.297 --> 33:55.766
<i> # And the true love</i>
<i> you'll find</i>

33:58.804 --> 34:01.972
<i> # You think that true love</i>

34:01.974 --> 34:05.108
<i> # Is your first love of life #</i>

34:23.362 --> 34:24.795
Don't waste my time.

34:24.797 --> 34:26.463
-Tell me now.
-Tell you what?

34:26.465 --> 34:28.999
Tell me
if there's something in it.

34:29.635 --> 34:30.901
Okay, maybe I should turn
this over

34:30.903 --> 34:32.436
to someone who won't be
so patient like I have.

34:32.438 --> 34:34.771
-There's nothing.
-Thank you.

34:34.773 --> 34:38.108
I appreciate that.
I'll bag this and label it.

34:38.110 --> 34:41.278
It's not a cheap one.
I'm sure you'd like it back.

34:42.681 --> 34:46.983
Talk about wasting your time,
you are wasting it in here.

34:47.252 --> 34:48.485
You're a real nice piece.

34:48.487 --> 34:50.987
You ought to try
peddling it out there.

34:50.989 --> 34:54.891
Bet you'd make five times the
scratch you get in this dump.

34:54.893 --> 34:56.827
Oh, you're right
about that, missus.

34:57.463 --> 34:58.995
Oh, you hear the lady?

34:58.997 --> 35:01.531
Scratch for the having
out there.

35:03.602 --> 35:06.203
You see something
you like, Officer?

35:07.306 --> 35:08.438
No, sir.

35:08.440 --> 35:11.041
But I was wondering,
those pants?

35:11.577 --> 35:13.477
Do they make them
for men, too?

35:13.479 --> 35:14.778
-(LAUGHTER)
-Because I'll tell you,

35:14.780 --> 35:16.012
you should go back
to whatever store

35:16.014 --> 35:17.547
you bought them at
and tell them

35:17.549 --> 35:18.582
that you are
a police officer

35:18.584 --> 35:22.085
in a position of authority
that is very hard to maintain

35:22.087 --> 35:25.455
in a felonious pair
of ball-huggers.

35:25.991 --> 35:28.325
Spell your name
for me, dear.

35:29.261 --> 35:31.161
(LAUGHTER)

35:32.998 --> 35:35.198
-How'd it go?
-It was glory.

35:35.200 --> 35:37.367
It was rock fate. Mwah!

35:37.803 --> 35:39.169
Oh! Mwah!

35:39.171 --> 35:40.504
Oh, is must have been
a good day.

35:40.506 --> 35:42.873
Oh, one of the best days
of my life.

35:42.875 --> 35:44.875
Glad to hear it, darling.

35:45.277 --> 35:46.877
(MANSON LAUGHS)

35:47.679 --> 35:50.514
(CHUCKLES)
Whoo!

35:53.018 --> 35:54.684
Cop came by.

35:55.521 --> 35:57.120
Detective.

35:57.122 --> 35:58.722
Looking for Emma.

35:58.724 --> 36:00.857
Brought her mama with him.

36:02.027 --> 36:06.029
Well, did you talk
to the man?

36:06.031 --> 36:07.898
Give him another thought
to be thinking?

36:07.900 --> 36:10.167
-Of course I did.
-Good.

36:10.936 --> 36:13.203
But I don't think
it worked.

36:19.678 --> 36:21.077
Something the matter?

36:21.079 --> 36:24.247
Well, how could there be
after the day we just had?

36:24.616 --> 36:27.751
No. Nothing.

36:27.853 --> 36:31.188
We just gotta
head back out, so, um,

36:32.291 --> 36:33.890
come on.

36:35.294 --> 36:38.094
Now?
What's going on?

36:38.897 --> 36:41.298
It's getting crowded here.

36:41.300 --> 36:43.600
I got a lot
of patience, but I...

36:43.602 --> 36:47.270
I don't like it to be tested
for no good reason.

36:48.473 --> 36:49.973
Where are we going?

36:49.975 --> 36:53.677
I'm taking you and Sadie
on a little meander.

36:54.213 --> 36:56.780
Okay.
Is Katie coming?

36:57.449 --> 36:59.249
How long are we gonna
be gone?

36:59.251 --> 37:00.951
(GASPS)

37:04.990 --> 37:07.023
See, the only...

37:07.292 --> 37:10.560
The only way this is going
to work

37:10.729 --> 37:14.965
is if we can be individuals
so strong with each other

37:14.967 --> 37:17.934
that together we are one.

37:18.604 --> 37:19.869
Cherry.

37:19.871 --> 37:23.707
I'm not gonna remind you
of that too many more times.

37:50.669 --> 37:52.936
-(DOOR OPENING)
-Is that Ken?

37:52.938 --> 37:56.072
No, um, Maria and Yolanda,
the housekeepers.

37:56.074 --> 37:58.541
-We should...
-No, not yet.

37:59.578 --> 38:02.245
-Sam...
-Just a little longer.

38:02.247 --> 38:04.147
Don't make me go yet.

38:10.555 --> 38:12.389
CUTLER: Sam.

38:12.758 --> 38:14.724
There's some MPs here
to see you.

38:14.726 --> 38:16.359
About Walt.

38:16.361 --> 38:17.193
I'm sorry, I thought...

38:17.195 --> 38:20.163
My buddy told me
that, that it wasn't gonna...

38:20.165 --> 38:22.532
Look, she's his mother,
okay?

38:22.534 --> 38:24.434
Don't try
to get even with her

38:24.436 --> 38:25.769
or you know
what's gonna happen.

38:25.771 --> 38:28.104
She did it because she
loves him and you know it.

38:28.106 --> 38:30.407
Don't pull her in
any deeper.

38:40.018 --> 38:44.387
I told them we don't talk,
so divorce has its upsides.

38:46.058 --> 38:47.090
Piss off.

38:47.092 --> 38:49.693
You're in rare form
this evening.

38:49.695 --> 38:52.095
Did you get an actual doctor
to back up this bull

38:52.097 --> 38:53.797
about you being sick?

38:54.933 --> 38:57.000
I am sick, Sam.

38:58.470 --> 39:00.003
Is it serious?

39:00.339 --> 39:02.238
Diabetes.

39:04.309 --> 39:07.077
So they prescribed
Scotch and cigarettes?

39:07.079 --> 39:08.445
Anything else, Officer?

39:08.447 --> 39:10.680
-I want to see Walt.
-No idea where he is.

39:10.682 --> 39:14.117
And there it is, your first
lie of the conversation.

39:14.119 --> 39:16.619
I need to get to him
before the MPs.

39:16.621 --> 39:19.356
So you can convince him
to do the right thing?

39:19.358 --> 39:21.191
The way you told him going
to Vietnam is what you'd do

39:21.193 --> 39:23.326
-if you were his age?
-It is what I'd do if I...

39:23.328 --> 39:24.627
Why? Why?

39:24.629 --> 39:26.329
What do you think
it is over there?

39:26.331 --> 39:29.699
The sequel to World War II,
your glory days?

39:29.935 --> 39:31.735
It is, with a twist.

39:32.237 --> 39:34.137
We're the bad guys.

39:40.979 --> 39:42.345
(THUDDING)

39:42.414 --> 39:44.080
(GLASS SHATTERS)

39:44.082 --> 39:46.483
(DOOR OPENS)

39:55.360 --> 39:57.694
Charlie.
Did you just break...

39:57.963 --> 39:59.629
What are you doing here?

40:02.401 --> 40:04.000
What is this?
Why are you here?

40:04.002 --> 40:05.635
I brought you
a present.

40:07.773 --> 40:09.806
Two presents.

40:11.543 --> 40:13.376
I don't understand.

40:13.745 --> 40:14.978
Oh, I'll, uh...

40:14.980 --> 40:16.646
I'll stay long enough
to make sure

40:16.648 --> 40:19.249
there's no static, but, uh...

40:19.518 --> 40:21.451
But they're yours, man...

40:22.053 --> 40:24.053
For as long
as you want 'em.

40:30.362 --> 40:31.294
(CHUCKLES)

40:31.296 --> 40:34.164
You shared your good
with me, man.

40:34.766 --> 40:36.733
Now I'm sharing mine.

40:51.082 --> 40:53.817
Just tell me.
Tell me anything.

40:53.819 --> 40:54.984
Just stop.
Will you stop?

40:54.986 --> 40:56.119
Where you were,
where you go,

40:56.121 --> 40:57.987
what you think,
who you are.

40:57.989 --> 41:00.156
(PHONE RINGING)

41:05.230 --> 41:08.331
MANSON: <i> I knew you'd want</i>
<i> to hear this, Kenny.</i>

41:08.667 --> 41:11.067
<i> I knew you'd be waiting to.</i>

41:11.937 --> 41:16.139
Something so beautiful
from something so ugly.

41:16.775 --> 41:18.775
<i> And all because of you.</i>

